47,25,46,28,42]} 1. e4 e5 2. Bc4 Nf6 3. d3 ({I noticed one interesting game
played in the Vienna} 3. Nc3 Nc6 4. d3 Bc5 5. f4 {Usually this is what White
wants to achieve.} d5 $5 {A very curious move. In this position, the
continuation} 6. Nxd5 {this looks critical} Ng4 7. f5 $1 $146 {This move is
actually a novelty.} ({Previously White has played} 7. Nh3 Qh4+ 8. Kf1 {
1/2-1/2 (37) Preziuso,T (2344)-Vitkevicius,J (2335) ICCF email 2007 Black
could have followed up with} Nf2 9. Qe1 Bxh3 10. Be3 Bxe3 11. Nxe3 exf4 12. Nd5
O-O-O $13) 7... h5 8. Nh3 Na5 9. b4 Nxc4 10. bxc5 c6 11. dxc4 cxd5 12. cxd5 {
1/2-1/2 (47) Amdouni,Z (2218)-Nyback,T (2579) Batumi GEO 2018 [Contora]} (12.
Qxd5 Bd7 13. O-O Bc6 $44) 12... Qh4+ 13. Kf1 Nf6 14. Nf2 Nxe4 $11) 3... c6 4.
Nf3 d5 5. Bb3 a5 {This is a very popular move for Black. The idea is to
provoke the advance a2-a4. This way, the b3-bishop may lose stability.} 6. a4
Bb4+ 7. c3 Bd6 {Now the white knight cannot go to c3, thus increasing the
pressure against the black center.} 8. exd5 Nxd5 {this seems like a good
alternative to the much more common} (8... cxd5) 9. O-O O-O 10. Re1 (10. Nbd2
Bc7 {was fine for Black in Klek,H (2326)-Nestorovic,N (2507) Germany 2016})
10... Re8 11. Bg5 $146 {This looks more challenging than the previously played}
(11. Nbd2 Nd7 12. Ne4 Bc7 13. d4 h6 $1 14. Ng3 exd4 15. Rxe8+ Qxe8 16. Bxd5
cxd5 17. Nxd4 Nf6 {and Black equalised in Nevednichy,V (2528)-Leventic,I (2411)
Mali Losinj 2017}) 11... f6 12. Bh4 Be6 13. Nbd2 Nd7 {Nabaty,T (2692)-Fridman,
D (2591) Batumi 2018} (13... Na6 $5 {could be a possible improvement.}) {
Now White missed a very interesting tactical idea} 14. d4 $5 $146 {with the
following point} exd4 15. Rxe6 $1 Rxe6 16. Nxd4 {White's threat of 17.c4 is
very powerful.} Re5 (16... Re8 {loses to} 17. c4) 17. c4 Nc5 18. cxd5 Nxb3 19.
Qxb3 Rxd5 20. Ne2 {White is better.} *

