) 12... Qxf5 13. b4 $1 {This is a very interesting idea. White challenges
Black's pawn structure, thus trying to gain control over the d4-square.} O-O
14. bxc5 Bxc5 15. Be3 Bxe3 16. Rxe3 Rad8 {1/2-1/2 (93) Anton Guijarro,D (2639)
-Nisipeanu,L (2661) Batumi GEO 2018 It looks like} 17. Nd4 $146 {could be a
better move. After} Nxd4 18. Qxd4 b6 19. a4 {White has a slight pull.}) 3... d6
4. Nf3 ({I have to mention the interesting alternative} 4. Nc4 Nxe4 5. Qe2 {
which recently has been played quite often} Qe7 6. Ne3 Be6 {A solid choice,
however, the move 7...Nc6, played by Caruana in the World Championship Match
against Carlsen, is much more convincing.} 7. Nc3 Nf6 8. g3 d5 $146 ({
