with a very complicated game in Rapport,R (2702)-Wei,Y (2706) Wijk aan Zee 2017
}) 9. Bg2 c6 10. d4 g6 11. O-O Bg7 {Black achieved a reliable position and
White is trying to create some complications} 12. f4 Na6 13. a3 Nc7 14. Bd2
O-O-O {and Black was doing very well in Kovalev,V (2664)-Smirnov,A (2549)
Batumi GEO 2018}) 4... Nxe4 5. d4 ({Recentely, the move} 5. Nc3 {is gradually
becoming a main line. In this position, I found two interesting games} Nxc3 6.
dxc3 Be7 7. Be3 Nc6 {Recently I have noticed the tendency of White to try to
fight for an advantage with moves other than the well-known 8. Qd2.} 8. Bd3 ({
