fantastic score in this position. Nevertheless Black's position is reliable
and he has a few solid options. The following one deserves serious attention.}
Nxc3 16. Qxc3 Bxd3 17. Qxd3 Qd7 18. Nh4 $146 ({Befor White tried} 18. b4 Qf5 (
18... Ng6 $5 {followed by 19...f6 is a very good alternative to the text.}) 19.
Qb3 f6 20. b5 fxe5 21. Nxe5 {Levitsky,A (2155)-Chkhaidze,N (2306) Prague 2018
Now Black should have vacated the f5-square for his knight by playing} Qe6 $1 {
with decent play.}) 18... f6 19. Rae1 (19. f4 Bc7 {would lead to a very
complex pawn structure.}) 19... fxe5 20. dxe5 Qe6 {Black obtained a good
position in Le,Q (2715)-Hansen,E (2629) Batumi GEO 2018} *

