1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 {There have been several interesting games in the Tarrasch
variation.} 3. Nd2 Nf6 (3... Be7 4. Ngf3 Nf6 5. e5 Nfd7 6. Bd3 c5 7. c3 Nc6 8.
O-O a5 {Very popular move, but it seems like Black has been struggling
recently. The only game didn't change this evaluation} 9. a4 Qb6 {A very
important model game in this line} (9... cxd4 10. cxd4 Nb4 11. Be2 O-O 12. Nb1
$1 {White's knight is heading to c3, where it covers the queenside, preventing
Black from possibly gaining counterplay over the c-file. Meanwhile White can
easily seize the initiative on the kingisde, mainly thanks to his space
advantage on this flank.} Nb6 13. Nc3 Bd7 14. b3 Rc8 15. Bd2 f6 16. Rc1 Be8 17.
exf6 Bxf6 18. Bf4 Bg6 19. Qd2 $16 {1-0 (44) Demchenko,A (2629)-Pourramezanali,
A (2522) Mersin 2016}) 10. dxc5 Qc7 11. Nb3 {A favourable line for White,
which has been proven once again in the following game} Ncxe5 12. Bf4 Nxf3+ 13.
Qxf3 Qd8 14. Qg3 $1 O-O 15. Bc7 Qe8 16. Bb5 $16 {White was clearly better in
Seps,M (2230)-Efroimski,M (2313) Batumi 2018}) 4. e5 Nfd7 5. Bd3 c5 6. c3 b6 {
