experiencing some problems.} 7. Ne2 Ba6 8. Bxa6 Nxa6 9. Nf3 Nc7 $6 (9... Be7 {
is a much more popular move and indeed looks more reliable.}) 10. h4 $1 {
I like this approach, White is perfectly fine staying with his king on f1 if
necessarry.} Nb8 $146 {Previously Black tried} (10... Qc8 {Mainka,R (2476)
-Buchenau,F (2220) Bad Zwesten 2000 I believe White should retain a pleasant
edge after} 11. h5 $146 h6 12. Rh3) 11. Nf4 Nc6 12. Kf1 ({Already here White
could have played} 12. Nh5 $1 {with the following nice point} Qd7 (12... h6 13.
Rh3 {and the idea 14. Rg3 is very annoying.}) 13. Bg5 h6 14. Bf6 $1 Rg8 15. O-O
{with a substantial advantage for White.}) 12... Qd7 13. g3 ({Once again} 13.
Nh5 {was quite strong} O-O-O 14. Rh3 $14) 13... f6 $13 {Black emerged from the
opening with a decent position. Cheparinov,I (2715)-Lopez Martinez,J (2581)
Batumi GEO 2018} *

